<p class="govuk-body">
  You could be eligible for either:
</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li data-qa="course__scholarship_amount">a scholarship of <%= number_to_currency(course.scholarship_amount) %></li>
  <li data-qa="course__bursary_amount">a bursary of <%= number_to_currency(course.bursary_amount) %></li>
</ul>

<% if course.has_early_career_payments? %>
  <p class="govuk-body">
    With a scholarship or bursary, you’ll also get early career payments of £5,000 each in your third and fifth year of teaching (£7,500 in <%= link_to 'some areas of England', 'https://www.gov.uk/guidance/mathematics-early-career-payments-guidance-for-teachers-and-schools', class: "govuk-link" %>).
  </p>
<% end %>

<p class="govuk-body">
  To qualify for a scholarship you’ll need a degree of 2:1 or above in <%= course.subjects.first %> or a related subject. For a bursary you’ll need a 2:2 or above in any subject.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
  You can’t claim both a bursary and a scholarship - you can only claim one.
</p>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Find out how to <%= link_to 'apply for a scholarship', 'https://getintoteaching.education.gov.uk/funding-and-salary/overview/scholarships', class: 'govuk-link' %>. You don’t need to apply for a bursary - if you’re eligible, you’ll automatically start receiving it once you begin your course. Find out <%= link_to 'how you’ll be paid', 'https://getintoteaching.education.gov.uk/funding-and-salary/overview/how-you-will-be-paid', class: 'govuk-link' %>.
</p>
